<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AFC G-05914 - Transmission Shift Cable Exposure to the Exhaust Manifold in CF 500 and CF 600 Models Built
        Between January 1, 2005 and July 14, 2005
    </stitle>
    <afc id="afc05914">
        <afcnum>G-05914</afcnum>
        <afcdate>January, 2006</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>TRANSMISSION</subjectfile>
        <subject>Transmission Shift Cable Exposure to the Exhaust Manifold in CF 500 and CF 600 Models Built Between
            January 1, 2005 and July 14, 2005
        </subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>CF 500
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>01/01/2005</startdate>
                        <enddate>07/14/2005</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>CF 600
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>01/01/2005</startdate>
                        <enddate>07/14/2005</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The transmission shift cable is exposed to the heat from the exhaust manifold and may result in
                    high shift lever effort.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <table id="t059141" tblwidth="pg-wide">
                <tgroup cols="3" align="center">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.76*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.51*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="0.74*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Part Number</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Description</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Quantity</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>8000879R91</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Heat Shield Kit, Contains the Following:</para>
                                <para>3565208R1, Heat Shield (1)</para>
                                <para>3564290C1, High Temperature Clamp (1)</para>
                                <para>289862C1, Cable Strap Lock (2)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2588838C2</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Shift Cable</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1</para>
                                <para>(See Note)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">NOTE:</emph>
                Replace the shift cable only if there are signs of shift cable heat damage and/or hard transmission
                shifting.
            </para>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="5">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury or death allow the vehicle to cool sufficiently before performing
                        this Service Procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the transmission shift lever and remove the cotter pin from the adjuster that
                    connects the shift cable to the transmission shift lever (Figure 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f059141" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g059141.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="168px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Remove Cotter Pin</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Cotter Pin</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Transmission Shift Lever</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Shift Cable Adjuster</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Shift Cable</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift cable from the transmission shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift cable clamp from the transmission housing (Figure 2). Remove the clamp
                    from the shift cable.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f059142" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g059142.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="168px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Remove Clamp from Shift Cable (Arrows)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the clamp from the frame mounted bracket and the shift cable (Figure 3).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f059143" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g059143.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="168px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Remove Clamp from Shift Cable (Arrow)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the shift cable for signs of heat damage and/or the shift lever in the cab moves
                    hard.
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If there are no signs of heat damage and the cab shift lever moves easy, continue to the
                            next Step.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If there are signs of heat damage and/or the cab shift lever moves hard, the shift cable
                            will need to be replaced.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <title>The Shift Cable has no Signs of Heat Damage and Shifts Easy</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mark the position of the adjuster jam nut on the shift cable (Figure 5, Item 2) and
                    remove the adjuster (Figure 5, Item 3) from the end of the shift cable.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install (slide) heat shield, Part Number 3565208R1, onto the shift cable (Figure 4)
                    until the adjuster end of the shift cable is as shown in Figure 5. Install a cable lock strap, Part
                    Number 289862C1, at each end of the heat shield.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f059144" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g059144.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Install (Slide) Heat Shield onto Shift Cable</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f059145" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g059145a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Heat Shield Properly Installed</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Cable Adjuster</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Adjuster Jam Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Heat Shield at End of Cable Housing</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the adjuster to the shift cable. Tighten the jam nut to 80 to 98 Lbf-in (9 to
                    11 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the shift cable to the transmission shift lever with a new cotter pin.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using the hardware from Step 3, attach the shift cable to the transmission housing.
                    Tighten to 80 to 98 Lbf-in (9 to 11 Nm)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use high temperature clamp, Part Number 3564290C1, to attach the shift cable to the
                    frame bracket (ref. Step 4). Tighten to 80 to 98 Lbf-in (9 to 11 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the shift cable for proper operation.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <title>For Cables with Signs of Heat damage and/or Hard Shifting</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove, install, and adjust the transmission shift cable following the procedure in
                    Service Section S13036, Pages 320 through 331.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install replacement shift cable, Part Number 2588838C2,. Include heat shield, Part
                    Number 3565208R1 high temperature clamp Part Number 3564290C1, and cable lock straps, Part Number
                    289862C1 following Steps 7 - 12.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
